Normalized Probabilistic Rand (NPR) Index

In this section, we outline the Normalized Probabilistic Rand (NPR) index, an extension to the Probabilistic Rand (PR) index proposed in [14]. Section 3.1 describes the PR index and further discusses its desirable properties. Section 3.2 explains a simpliﬁcation required for further analysis. Finally, Section 3.3 presents the NPR, describing its crucial improvements over the PR and other segmentation measures.

