[cij pij + (1 − cij )(1 − pij )]

(3) This measure takes values in [0, 1], where 0 means Stest and {S1 , S2 , . . . , SK } have no similarities (i.e. when S consists of a single cluster and each segmentation in {S1 , S2 , . . . , SK } consists only of clusters containing single points, or vice versa) to 1 when all segmentations are identical.

