The question is: what is a meaningful way to compute S S pi,j = E I li test = lj test ? We propose that for a baseline in image segmentation to be useful, it must be representative of perceptually consistent grouping of random but realistic images. Pair-wise probabilities provide a convenient way to model such segmentations of natural images. This translates to estimating pij from segmentations of all images for all unordered pairs (i, j). Let Φ be the number of images in a dataset, and Kφ the number of ground truth hand segmentations of image φ. Then pij can be expressed as: pij = 1 Φ 1 Kφ
